{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b648f9e7-3365-4109-ac79-3b2c18883ac2","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_RUlOmGvRpSgIpigGIZPovI","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-0bac0547007d4d559440e8c5c1882fdf/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-0bac0547007d4d559440e8c5c1882fdf/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"7ca4d157-dbe1-45f2-83e4-05eb24e52093","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, meaning it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, this will fail.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":470,"requestId":"DBCB:32F6A4:15ABC9A:1841833:69FD340B"},"id":"b49fcfe1-3837-4677-ae23-0135f74a7a46","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:39.750Z","parentId":"83ba113b-5ff3-4bfd-9782-d25848cbb1e9"}
